var custom_content = `<meta charset='utf-8'/><div class="headword">amalgamation</div><div class="blurb"><p class="short">You create an <i>amalgamation</i> by taking separate things and combining them into one. If your school is closing and joining with another school to create a new school, that is an <i>amalgamation</i>.</p><p class="long">Commonly, amalgamation is a term used to describe the merger of two or more companies into one. Before J.P Morgan Chase was a single bank (or an amalgamation), it was two separate entities: J.P. Morgan and the Chase Manhattan Corporation. When you want to describe something as being made up of many previously separate parts, you can say it's an amalgamation.</p></div>`;
